properties.headline: Flood Advisory issued February 3 at 8:35PM CST until February 4 at 8:30PM CST by NWS Omaha/Valley NE
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Omaha has issued a

* Flood Advisory for...
An Ice Jam in...
North central Dodge County in east central Nebraska...

* Until 830 PM CST Tuesday.

* At 835 PM CST, minor flooding was likely still occurring on parts
of the Elkhorn River. Earlier in the day Monday, emergency
management reported an ice jam that started at the bend in the
river at Powder Horn State Wildlife Management Area north of
Scribner. The jam extended upstream to about 300 yards west of the
Highway 275 bridge near Crowell. Crowell is between Scribner and
West Point. This is an extension of the previous flood advisory.

* Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Rural areas near Scribner, Powder Horn State Wildlife Management
Area and Dead Timber State Recreation Area.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Advisory means river or stream flows are elevated, or ponding
of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent.
